From c4aa47522a8a9814fb2f8c07fedcc33ab5054495 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.local>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 23:19:36 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Redesign the visual system: The Pass
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replaces the templated cream/serif/coral look with an identity grounded in
the product's own world — a back-of-house instrument for service.

- Palette: deep spruce shell (evolving the sage heritage), porcelain
  content surface, and a flame accent reserved for primary actions and the
  live signal. Semantic sage/amber/red recalibrated for AA contrast; the
  primary CTA gradient is bottom-weighted so white text holds contrast.
- Typography: Archivo (signage grotesque) replaces Georgia for display and
  Inter for UI; Spline Sans Mono sets every figure — currency, percentages,
  dates, statuses, site codes, step markers, table headers — as the docket
  voice with tabular numerals. Fonts load via preconnected stylesheet links
  so builds never depend on a font fetch.
- Signature: weekly report rows are rail dockets — status spine, punched
  hole, lift on hover. Metric cards get a staggered entrance (reduced
  motion respected) and hover elevation.
- Global :focus-visible ring, refined buttons with pressed states, quieter
  chips/badges, spruce login hero with a distant flame ember, and the last
  inline Georgia heading moved into the design system.
---
